The paper deals with the problem of finding a drawing of a planar graph with a set of additional edges that minimizes the number of pairwise edge crossings. This problem is closely related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and approximation bounds, which are topics in theoretical computer science (cs.TC) and combinatorics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper mentions the crossing number problem, which is a well-studied problem in graph theory and computational complexity (cs.CC).
